text: Demopsestis yoshimotoi is a moth in the family Drepanidae. It was described by Gyula M. László, Gábor Ronkay, László Aladár Ronkay and Thomas Joseph Witt in 2007. It is found in Thailand.Laszlo, Gy. M.; Ronkay, G.; Ronkay, L. & Witt, T. (2007). "The Thyatiridae of Eurasia including the Sundaland and New Guinea (Lepidoptera)". Esperiana Buchreihe zur Entomologie. 13: 1-683. Archived October 5, 2008. ==References== Category:Moths described in 2007 Category:Thyatirinae Category:Moths of Thailand
